    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Window or door shutters having louvers, which are horizontal slats that are movable and may be angled to admit light and air, but to keep out rain and snow. The louvers are set into a frame to make a shutter.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
